Package: tt-toplike
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: tt-smi, tenstorrent-dkms
Suggests: tt-toplike-egui, tenstorrent-tools
Description: Real-time hardware monitoring TUI for Tenstorrent silicon
 tt-toplike is a terminal-based monitoring tool for Tenstorrent hardware
 (Grayskull, Wormhole, Blackhole). Multiple visualization modes provide
 psychedelic real-time views of hardware telemetry:
 .
  - arcade: unified split-screen with all three visualizations
  - castle: memory hierarchy (DDR channels, L2 cache, Tensix cores)
  - starfield: Tensix cores as stars (brightness = power, colour = temp)
  - flow: NoC particles and DDR perimeter animation
  - normal: traditional telemetry table
 .
 Uses safe, non-invasive backends by default. Direct hardware access via
 Luwen (PCI BAR0) is available only via --backend luwen and should never
 be used while workloads are running.
 .
 Backend auto-detection order:
  - sysfs:  Linux hwmon sensors — zero interference, no permissions needed
  - json:   tt-smi subprocess (requires tt-smi package from TT PPA)
  - mock:   simulated telemetry, no hardware required

Package: tt-toplike-egui
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: tt-toplike, libvulkan1 | libgl1
Description: Psychedelic egui dashboard for Tenstorrent hardware monitoring
 A GPU-accelerated egui companion dashboard to tt-toplike. Features 150
 animated particles, a TRON grid overlay, cyberpunk-themed real-time charts,
 and a process monitoring panel.
 .
 Requires a Vulkan or OpenGL-capable GPU and a graphical display (Wayland
 or X11). Not suitable for headless / server installs — use tt-toplike
 (the TUI) for those environments.
